'''Umajiisobe Shrine''' (うまじいそべじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Moriyama|Q857225|WD=Q857225|1=Moriyama, Shiga}}, {{ill|lt=Shiga Prefecture|Q131358|WD=Q131358|1=Shiga Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}}, and under the former {{ill|lt=modern shrine ranking system|Q712534|WD=Q712534|lt=shrine ranking system|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines}} its rank was {{ill|lt=Gōsha|Q134917316|WD=Q134917316|1=Gō-sha}}. Its shrine crest is the "mokkō".

=== Enshrined deities ===
The principal deities are the following two:
* '''{{ill|lt=Susanoo|Q272993|WD=Q272993|lt=Takehaya Susanoo-no-Mikoto|1=Susanoo-no-Mikoto}}'''
* '''{{ill|lt=Ōkuninushi|Q276944|WD=Q276944|lt=Ōanamuji-no-Mikoto|1=Ōkuninushi}}'''

=== History ===
It is said to have been founded in {{ill|lt=Hakuhō|Q11580612|WD=Q11580612|1=Hakuhō}} 3 ({{ill|lt=663|Q31122|WD=Q31122|1=663}}), during the reign of {{ill|lt=Emperor Tenmu|Q335181|WD=Q335181|1=Emperor Tenmu}}, and that in {{ill|lt=Shuchō|Q777413|WD=Q777413|1=Shuchō}} 1 ({{ill|lt=686|Q30619|WD=Q30619|1=686}}) Ōanamuji-no-Mikoto was {{ill|lt=jointly enshrined|Q11412524|WD=Q11412524|1=Co-Enshrinement}}. In ancient times, it was worshipped as the {{ill|lt=ujigami|Q767655|WD=Q767655|1=Ujigami}} by the {{ill|lt=Isobe no Kimi clan|UNKNOWN|lt=Isobe-no-Kimi}} family, a {{ill|lt=local powerful clan|Q84066|WD=Q84066|1=Gōzoku}} based in {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Umaji-gō|1=UNKNOWN}}.

In the mid-{{ill|lt=Heian period|Q193292|WD=Q193292|1=Heian period}}, the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}} lists it as "Umajiisobe Shrine, Yasu District, {{ill|lt=Ōmi Province|Q843882|WD=Q843882|1=Ōmi Province}}," placing it among shikinaisha. In the medieval period, as the {{ill|lt=guardian shrine|Q13479654|WD=Q13479654|1=Chinjusha}} of {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Tanaka-no-shō|1=UNKNOWN}}, it was called "Tanaka Daimyōjin" and "Tanaka Tennō-sha."

In the Sengoku period, it was revered by the {{ill|lt=Rokkaku clan|Q2975342|WD=Q2975342|1=Rokkaku clan}}, but shrine buildings were lost in the conflicts of {{ill|lt=Genki|Q1145064|WD=Q1145064|1=Genki (era)}} and {{ill|lt=Tenshō|Q1145058|WD=Q1145058|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)}}. It was rebuilt in the {{ill|lt=Edo period|Q184963|WD=Q184963|1=Edo period}}, and the current buildings date to {{ill|lt=Bunkyū|Q730266|WD=Q730266|1=Bunkyū}} 2 ({{ill|lt=1862|Q7698|WD=Q7698|1=1862}}).

In {{ill|lt=Meiji|Q3125096|WD=Q3125096|1=Meiji era}} 9 ({{ill|lt=1876|Q7766|WD=Q7766|1=1876}}), it was ranked village shrine in the {{ill|lt=modern shrine ranking system|Q712534|WD=Q712534|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines}}, and in Meiji 14 it was promoted to {{ill|lt=Gōsha|Q134917316|WD=Q134917316|1=Gō-sha}}.

=== Precincts ===
<gallery widths="200px" heights="150px">
ファイル:馬路石邊神社 拝殿.JPG|'''Haiden'''
ファイル:馬路石邊神社 神門.JPG|'''Shinmon gate'''
ファイル:馬路石邊神社 鳥居.JPG|'''Torii'''
</gallery>

The current shrine buildings were constructed in {{ill|lt=Bunkyū|Q730266|WD=Q730266|1=Bunkyū}} 2 ({{ill|lt=1862|Q7698|WD=Q7698|1=1862}}).

Along the approach stands a "Mikoshi-zuka" mound said to contain a buried mikoshi.

=== Subsidiary shrines ===
[[ファイル:馬路石邊神社 摂末社.JPG|thumb|right|220px|Subsidiary shrines]]
The subsidiary shrines are grouped on the east side of the precincts.
* Kotoshironushi Shrine - deity: {{ill|WD=Q8009611|lt=Kotoshironushi|Q8009611|WD=Q8009611|WD=Q8009611|lt=Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto|1=Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto}}
* Sumiyoshi Shrine - deities: {{ill|lt=Sumiyoshi Sanjin|Q1114013|WD=Q1114013|lt=Sokotsutsu-no-o-no-Mikoto / Nakatsutsu-no-o-no-Mikoto / Uwatsutsu-no-o-no-Mikoto|1=Sumiyoshi sanjin}}
* Shinmei Shrine - deity: {{ill|lt=Amaterasu|Q455602|WD=Q455602|lt=Amaterasu Kōtaimikami|1=Amaterasu}}
* Hachiman Shrine - deity: {{ill|lt=Emperor Ojin|Q317997|WD=Q317997|lt=Homuda-wake-no-Mikoto|1=Emperor Ōjin}}
* Sannō Shrine - deity: {{ill|WD=Q10935105|lt=Ōyamakui-no-Kami|Q10935105|WD=Q10935105|WD=Q10935105|lt=Ōyamakui-no-Mikoto|1=Oyamakui no Kami}}
* Inari Shrine - deity: {{ill|WD=Q3080728|lt=Ukanomitama|Q3080728|WD=Q3080728|WD=Q3080728|lt=Ukanomitama-no-Mikoto|1=Ukanomitama}}
* Atago Shrine - deity: {{ill|lt=Kagutsuchi|Q1640658|WD=Q1640658|lt=Homusubi-no-Kami|1=Kagu-tsuchi}}

=== Main festivals ===
* Spring festival (May 4-5)<ref name="guide">{{Cite web|title="Nakasendō Moriyama-juku" complete guidebook|url=https://www.city.moriyama.lg.jp/_res/projects/default_project/_page_/001/004/384/gai.pdf |page=4|website=Moriyama and Yoshimi district revitalization committee |accessdate=2025-03-18 |language=ja}}</ref>
*: On May 5, the Hōnen-odori (Moriyama City designated intangible folk cultural property) is offered<ref name="guide" />.
* Autumn festival (third Saturday in October)<ref name="guide" />
*: Sōmoku Sentō (kyōgen offering) is performed<ref name="guide" />.

